paragraph.text:
medical debt is
			 unique, and Americans do not choose when accidents happen or when illness
			 strikes;

nevertheless,
			 medical debt that has been completely paid off or settled can significantly
			 damage the credit score of a consumer for years;

as a result,
			 consumers may be denied credit or pay higher interest rates when buying a home
			 or obtaining a credit card;

in fact, medical
			 bills account for more than half of all non-credit related collection actions
			 reported to consumer credit reporting agencies;
